                <head>193. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>On September 25, Prime Minister S.W.R.D. <persName corresp="#p_BMS1"
                        >Bandaranaike</persName> was shot and fatally wounded. He died the following
                    day. On September 26, <persName corresp="#p_DW1">Wijeyananda
                        Dahanayake</persName>, the Minister of Education, formed a new government,
                    retaining all the ministers from the <persName corresp="#p_BMS1"
                        >Bandaranaike</persName> government.</p>
                <p>On October 1, at the 420th meeting of the National Security Council, <persName
                        corresp="#p_DAW1">Allen Dulles</persName> discussed this development during
                    his survey of significant world developments affecting U.S. security: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“Mr. <persName corresp="#p_DAW1">Dulles</persName> believed the
                            assassination of the Prime Minister in Ceylon would have no great
                            political consequence, inasmuch as it appeared to be the act of a
                            fanatic for personal not national reasons. The Prime Minister’s
                            successor would not have the prestige, standing in the party or grasp of
                            foreign problems possessed by <persName corresp="#p_BMS1"
                                >Bandaranaike</persName>. The result might be a weak central
                            authority, followed by another change in the government.” (Memorandum of
                            discussion by Marion W. Boggs, October 2; Eisenhower Library, Whitman
                            File, <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Records)</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Documentation on the assassination of <persName corresp="#p_BMS1"
                        >Bandaranaike</persName> and the accession of <persName corresp="#p_DW1"
                        >Dahanayake</persName> to the Prime Ministership is in Department of State,
                    Central File 746E.00.</p>
            </div>
